From Wim Van Holder Subject Re WINQVTNET with NDIS on Token Ring In article APR DATAMARK CO NZ , writes In article A Wim Van Holder writes Is it possible to use WinQVT Net on a machine that uses NDIS to connect to a Token Ring I tried it with older versions but got an invalid packet class error or something the like How are you attempting to do that Are you using the DIS PKT program This provides a packet driver on top of the NDIS driver I tried to do so, but people told me that even if I used DISPKT, the packets would still be incompatible Is this true Thomas Beagle Work o Technical Writer Home , Wellington, NZ Hound for hire Will work for dog biscuits Wim Van Holder Katholieke Universiteit Leuven Tel Departement T E W FAX Dekenstraat B Leuven E mail BELGIUM